<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-07T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-07T04:00:00-05:00" n="286" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d286">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/774</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-07T18:00:00+09:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 7, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 8, 2.55
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Russian Ambassador informs me he has received a peremptory telegram
                                from Petrograd signed by <persName corresp="#p_TLDB1">Trotsky</persName> directing him either formally to acknowledge
                                the authority of the group governing Russia, or to transfer the
                                affairs of the Embassy to any other member of the staff who is in
                                sympathy and acknowledges the authority of the Maximalists. The
                                Ambassador has reported the matter to the Minister of Foreign
                                Affairs who assures him that he will continue to recognize him as
                                Russian representative.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MRS1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>